This paper deals with the problem of typing dynamic languages, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also introduces a new framework for typing, which could potentially fall under logic in computer science (cs.LO) and type theory (cs.TP). Finally, the paper uses refinement typing, which is a technique commonly used in program analysis and verification (cs.CL).
